<h2 id="how-to-enable-expert-settings-in-xbmchttpswwwmasoopycomtagxbmc--kodihttpswwwmasoopycomtagkodi">How to enable Expert Settings in <a href="https://www.masoopy.com/tag/xbmc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer ">#XBMC</a> / <a href="https://www.masoopy.com/tag/kodi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreffer ">#Kodi</a></h2>
<p>Navigate to <em>System</em> &gt; <em>Settings</em>. From here notice the <em>Basic settings</em> button in the bottom left corner.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Navigate to it (yes, you can!) and just press your Return keyboard’s key. You’ll see that the button now reads <em>Expert settings</em>.</p>
<p>Job’s done!</p>
